}{}${\rm TermSet} = \{ { {\rm HP}_1,{\rm HP}_2, \ldots ,{\rm HP}_n} \}$\end{document}, each HPO term is assigned a weight representing the granularity of phenotypic information given by the HPO term. In each HPj’s candidate gene list, every candidate gene has a score calculated by Enhanced Phenolyzer. It is a quantitative representation of how genei is associated with HPj. Phen2Gene gives a weighted score to genei, if genei is in HPj’s candidate gene list,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
