}{}$$\begin{eqnarray*}{S_{{\rm weighted}}} \left( {{\rm gene}_i} \right) &=& \mathop \sum \limits_{j = 1}^n W\left( {{\rm HP}_j} \right) \times S\left( {{\rm gene}_i,{\rm HP}_j} \right),\\ &&{\rm where}\ {\rm HP}_j \in \left\{ {{\rm HP}_1,{\rm HP}_2, \ldots ,{\rm HP}_n} \right\},\end{eqnarray*}$$\end{document}where W(HPj) is the assigned weight as illustrated in the previous section, S(genei, HPj) is genei’s score in HPj’s candidate gene list. S(genei, HPj) = 0, if genei is not a candidate gene of HPj. All of genes are sorted by their scores in descending order.
